p28
a. 
Unable to establish connection.
When the TCPClient starts, it will try to establish a TCP connection. If the TCPServer does not start, the connection establishment fails.
b. 
No problem. 
There is no need to establish any connection between the UDPClient and the UDPServer.
c. 
TCP: The TCPClient will try to establish a connection with the wrong process (or a process that doesn't exist at all), which will lead to an error.
UDP: Unable to send information to the correct process.
